# F1 line-ending policy.
#
# Why this file exists:
#   CSPro Designer (Windows) rewrites its owned artifacts with CRLF on every
#   File -> Save / F7 publish. The Python generators in this folder emit LF
#   because Python's open()/write() on Windows produces \n. Without per-file
#   pinning, each commit yields "warning: CRLF will be replaced by LF"
#   chatter that the data programmer has to scroll past.
#
# Strategy:
#   - Pin Designer-owned artifacts to eol=crlf so the index matches what
#     Designer writes, removing the round-trip warning.
#   - Pin generator-emitted sources (Python, regenerated JSON .ent, spec docs)
#     to eol=lf so git autocrlf does not add CR on checkout.
#
# Cross-platform note: macOS/Linux contributors will still see LF in their
# checkout for the lf-pinned files; the crlf-pinned files arrive as CRLF
# but those are touched only by CSPro Designer on Windows in practice.

# --- Designer-owned binaries (kept CRLF) ---------------------------------
*.dcf           text eol=crlf
*.fmf           text eol=crlf
*.ent.apc       text eol=crlf
*.ent.mgf       text eol=crlf
*.ent.qsf       text eol=crlf

# --- Generator-emitted sources (kept LF) ---------------------------------
*.py            text eol=lf
*.ent           text eol=lf
*.pff           text eol=lf
*.md            text eol=lf
.gitattributes  text eol=lf
